name: Higher and Higher
description: In a hot air balloon, we will fly! No fear, no thoughts that we might die. We love, we hope, we try to soar, higher and higher from the floor. With all things below becoming small, until our eyes can’t make out what’s what at all. We lean over the edge to touch a cloud “they’re made of tears!” we cry aloud. We exchange looks and hope that this wont be, the last flight between you and me. “This time won’t be the last” is what she’ll say, “We will see eachother again some other day.” The sky’s the limit, to the limit we’ll fly: until our lungs collapse and with smiles we’ll die. ©2007 secret ink. all rights reserved.

name: Beauty
description: You will always be beautiful, no matter what the people say. Not even the doctor who cradled you into this world can say otherwise, for you were beautiful before he laid his eyes upon you. You were beautiful from your very first heart beat, and to your very last breath, you will be beautiful. The people on the streets; they have yet to know true beauty, for they have yet to see you. But sight is not reliable. Sometimes we see things that are not truly there. Feelings and sounds are unreliable as well. Sometimes we hear and feel things that are fake, but you, you are a new kind of exception: a remarkable breakthrough that naturally occurred. Without even make-up or assistance, you are perfect. ©2007 secret ink. all rights reserved. this design is courtesy of the always remarkable marlo weekley!

name: Embrace
description: Under the ocean, the glistening waves, under the world caught up with greed. Under the world of mindless slaves, apart from that of fuel we feed. Here lie the diamonds, the worlds’ forgotten treasure. These creatures of the ocean who hunt to survive. Here exists not demand for pleasure, but rather true affection; affection so evident and clearly alive. They remember what we have forgotten: how to care, how to live, and how to be free. We claim ourselves the most intelligent breed, but we’re nothing more than walking irony. We sell time to buy money and sweat for breaks, to raise these children who will eventually do the same. We try to be real but are guided by fakes, and end up losing at this simple life game. If we would plunge under and away from the sin above, we might remember how it feels to love. ©2007 secret ink. all rights reserved.
